    "body": "@promag: Feel free to add my commit: https://github.com/theStack/bitcoin/commit/5dfc039e89107a261c7f8eda70bae1fe63c581c7 (branch https://github.com/theStack/bitcoin/tree/20200903-refactor-get-rid-of-boost-replace_first):\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/core_read.cpp b/src/core_read.cpp\r\nindex 1829f18..155f443 100644\r\n--- a/src/core_read.cpp\r\n+++ b/src/core_read.cpp\r\n@@ -15,7 +15,6 @@\r\n #include <version.h>\r\n\r\n #include <boost/algorithm/string/classification.hpp>\r\n-#include <boost/algorithm/string/replace.hpp>\r\n #include <boost/algorithm/string/split.hpp>\r\n\r\n #include <algorithm>\r\n@@ -40,8 +39,8 @@ opcodetype ParseOpCode(const std::string& s)\r\n                 continue;\r\n             mapOpNames[strName] = static_cast<opcodetype>(op);\r\n             // Convenience: OP_ADD and just ADD are both recognized:\r\n-            boost::algorithm::replace_first(strName, \"OP_\", \"\");\r\n-            mapOpNames[strName] = static_cast<opcodetype>(op);\r\n+            if (strName.rfind(\"OP_\", 0) == 0)\r\n+                mapOpNames[strName.substr(3)] = static_cast<opcodetype>(op);\r\n         }\r\n     }\r\n```\r\nAnother solution would be to use `if (strName.substr(0,3) == \"OP_\") ...`.",
